# 🐳 Python Docker API

A simple Flask-based REST API containerized using Docker and ready for deployment.

This project demonstrates how to build, package, and run a Python backend inside a Docker container — a real-world backend skill used in production environments.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Flask REST API
- Dockerized application
- Health check endpoint
- JSON API responses
- Production-ready setup using Gunicorn
- Ready for cloud deployment (Render, AWS, etc.)

---

## 📦 API Endpoints

### GET /
Returns basic API info

{
  "message": "Python Docker API is running",
  "status": "success",
  "routes": ["/health", "/tasks"]
}

---

### GET /health
Health check endpoint

{
  "status": "healthy",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-30T19:42:44"
}

---

### GET /tasks
Returns a list of sample tasks

{
  "count": 2,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Learn Docker basics",
      "completed": true
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "title": "Deploy Python app with Docker",
      "completed": false
    }
  ]
}

---

## 🐳 Running with Docker

### Build the image

docker build -t python-docker-app .

### Run the container

docker run -p 5001:5001 python-docker-app

### Open in browser

http://localhost:5001

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Python
- Flask
- Gunicorn
- Docker

---

## 🌐 Deployment

This project is designed to be deployed using Docker on platforms like:

- Render
- AWS (ECS / Elastic Beanstalk)
- Google Cloud Run
- Fly.io

---

## 📌 What This Project Demonstrates

- Containerizing a backend application with Docker
- Running a Python API in a production-ready environment
- Structuring a simple REST API
- Preparing an app for cloud deployment

